This paper discusses the functional requirements and challenges of mobility management in 5G networks, which are primarily related to networking and communication (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the potential solutions for 5G MM, which could fall under the categories of communication (cs.COMM), architecture (cs.AR), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
